# Documentation only — see the files below for real local configuration.
#
# This project uses two local credential files with different purposes:
#
# 1) .dev.vars (copy from .dev.vars.example)
#    Worker runtime bindings for `pnpm dev`.
#    Names are fixed by src/config/env.ts (AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID, MCP_AUTH_TOKEN, …).
#
# 2) .env.deploy.local (copy from .env.deploy.example)
#    Deploy credentials with AWS_MCP_GATEWAY_* prefixes so they do not clash
#    with other Cloudflare/AWS projects on your machine.
#    Use: pnpm run sync-secrets | pnpm run deploy:configured
#
# Production Worker secrets keep the runtime binding names above.
# The deploy script maps AWS_MCP_GATEWAY_* → Worker secret names for wrangler.
#
# Worker [vars] and OAuth configuration: copy wrangler.example.jsonc and replace
# placeholders (worker host, Auth0 issuer/JWKS, audience, KV namespace id).
# Never commit .dev.vars, .env, .env.deploy.local, Cloudflare API tokens,
# OAuth client secrets, or AWS keys.
#
# --- Auth modes ---
#
# Local legacy mode (default for pnpm dev):
#   AUTH_MODE=legacy-bearer
#   MCP_AUTH_TOKEN=
#
# Production ChatGPT OAuth mode (set in wrangler [vars] or dashboard):
#   AUTH_MODE=oauth
#   MCP_RESOURCE_URL=https://<worker-host>
#   OAUTH_ISSUER=https://<auth-provider-domain>/
#   OAUTH_AUDIENCE=https://<worker-host>
#   OAUTH_JWKS_URI=https://<auth-provider-domain>/.well-known/jwks.json
#   OAUTH_REQUIRED_SCOPES=aws:read
#
# See docs/auth-chatgpt-oauth.md for the full ChatGPT setup guide.
